HEADWORD: Recoupment
<hw>Re*coup"ment</hw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act
of recouping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Recoupment</xex> applies to equities growing out of
the very affair from which thw principal demand arises,
<xex>set-off</xex> to cross-demands which may be independent in
origin.</note> <rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

